Definition: a man or woman in the workplace with whom one shares a special relationship having bonds similar to those of a marriage: special confidences, loyalties, shared jokes and experiences, an unusual degree of honesty or openness. With so many of the quality hours of a day spent at work, having someone there who has an intuitive understanding of the pressures, personalities, interactions, and underlying narratives of the workplace society can add safety and comfort to what can otherwise be an alienating environment. The work spouse is a potentially key relationship when one's actual spouse or boy/girlfriend is not able to understand the nuances of the workplace and either cannot sufficiently comprehend the background to stories of the workday nor care about them sufficiently to provide a complex reaction. While it is not unusual for the relationship to contain elements of flirtation, this relationship can be threatened rather than enhanced if taken to the bedroom.

Also: work wife, work husband